        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 7 at 7:41PM CDT by NWS Tulsa OK</headline>
        <description>At 741 PM CDT, Doppler radar indicated a strong thunderstorm 3 miles
south of Watova, moving east at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down small tree limbs and blow
around unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation
is possible.

Locations in or near the path include...
Chelsea...                        New Alluwe...
Watova...                         Foyil...
Bushyhead...                      Oologah...

This includes Interstate 44 between mile markers 260 and 268.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Conditions are favorable for the development of weak, brief funnel
clouds. This type of funnel cloud is harmless, but on rare occasions
they can briefly touch down, producing wind gusts over 50 mph. If a
funnel cloud is spotted move indoors and report your sighting to the
National Weather Service.</instruction>
